The paper deals with a distributed algorithm for solving linear equations over a network of agents, which involves concepts from control theory (Lyapunov function), distributed computing (asynchronous interactions), networking (membership dynamics), and machine learning (convergence analysis). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
